1
00:00:01,547 --> 00:00:03,366
Okay.

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:06,720
A bigger job than I thought.

3
00:00:07,080 --> 00:00:10,500
They want us to scan and digitize
all the medical records here.

4
00:00:10,813 --> 00:00:12,870
How many decades' worth?

5
00:00:17,356 --> 00:00:20,846
Wait, isn't this the chairwoman?

6
00:00:22,650 --> 00:00:25,026
The chairwoman was a doctor?

7
00:00:25,026 --> 00:00:27,746
I may have heard something like that.

8
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:31,480
She was already chairwoman
by the time I joined.

9
00:00:34,856 --> 00:00:36,890
Shura Anno

10
00:00:41,236 --> 00:00:42,489
What are you doing?

11
00:00:44,163 --> 00:00:46,636
Wanna see, Anno?
Her younger days.

12
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:53,613
Incoming.

13
00:00:58,073 --> 00:00:59,200
Yes.

14
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:02,060
One pedestrian hit by a car.
Can you accept?

15
00:01:02,060 --> 00:01:03,460
Bring them in now.

16
00:01:04,653 --> 00:01:07,193
I can't see anything
through all this bleeding.

17
00:01:07,193 --> 00:01:08,326
- Suction.
- Yes.

18
00:01:08,326 --> 00:01:09,793
Clamping abdominal aorta.

19
00:01:09,793 --> 00:01:11,286
- Satinsky.
- Here.

20
00:01:19,540 --> 00:01:21,017
Bleeding's stopped.

21
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,820
Starting sutures. Kelly.

22
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,039
Yes.

23
00:01:32,876 --> 00:01:34,256
- Cooper.
- Yes.

24
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:39,150
Hemostasis complete.

25
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:47,608
Something's wrong.
The bleeding stopped, but BP isn't rising.

26
00:01:58,894 --> 00:02:01,654
- Digestive fluid leaking from posterior.
- What?

27
00:02:02,340 --> 00:02:04,160
The duodenum may be damaged.

28
00:02:04,242 --> 00:02:06,400
Dissect to examine the posterior duodenum.

29
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,880
- Long Cooper.
- Here.

30
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:20,466
Blood pressure is stable.

31
00:02:20,466 --> 00:02:22,946
We'll monitor and determine for reoperation.

32
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:24,268
Yes.

33
00:02:26,085 --> 00:02:27,110
Patient X

34
00:02:27,110 --> 00:02:29,110
We can't identify him?

35
00:02:29,276 --> 00:02:33,236
All he had was a wallet.
No driver's license or insurance card.

36
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:35,376
Excuse me.

37
00:02:35,755 --> 00:02:38,042
I hear police came to the ICU.

38
00:02:38,042 --> 00:02:39,514
What on earth happened?

39
00:02:39,514 --> 00:02:41,390
Oh, no, Dr. Kongo. It's not really...

40
00:02:41,390 --> 00:02:44,230
What is it then?
Did Ashura finally get herself arrested?

41
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:47,590
No, an unidentified patient was admitted.

42
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:51,770
An unidentified patient.
Sounds like trouble.

43
00:02:53,110 --> 00:02:55,650
Don't go causing
any unnecessary problems.

44
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:59,103
If anything, I'm the one held responsible
as Head of Medical.

45
00:02:59,383 --> 00:03:00,816
Yes, we'll be careful.

46
00:03:00,816 --> 00:03:03,900
But can the police actually
identify someone like that?

47
00:03:05,410 --> 00:03:07,084
Why are you asking me?

48
00:03:07,609 --> 00:03:09,253
Look it up yourself.

49
00:03:09,253 --> 00:03:11,166
- Sorry.
- Such an amateur move.

50
00:03:11,970 --> 00:03:16,635
If they're in the police database,
fingerprint matching can identify them.

51
00:03:16,635 --> 00:03:18,630
Wait, so they have a criminal record?

52
00:03:18,630 --> 00:03:20,203
Again, why ask me?

53
00:03:20,203 --> 00:03:23,029
You ask me with 100% chance.

54
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:28,230
Most likely, but they won't share
details due to privacy laws.

55
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:31,562
The hospital staff can't exactly ask,
"Are you a convict?"

56
00:03:31,562 --> 00:03:33,730
He wouldn't come out to say that himself.

57
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:36,508
True. Well, you're quite right.

58
00:03:36,674 --> 00:03:38,190
Let's have some tea and--

59
00:03:38,881 --> 00:03:41,781
Wait, no. That's not the point.

60
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:46,903
Either way, an unidentified patient
is nothing but a liability waiting to happen.

61
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:50,070
Make sure you keep a close eye
on that patient.

62
00:04:04,422 --> 00:04:05,622
I'm sorry!

63
00:04:19,930 --> 00:04:21,130
What?

64
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:23,730
Excuse me!

65
00:04:31,860 --> 00:04:33,510
Emergency department.

66
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:37,194
Dr. Anno. There's a call from the police.

67
00:04:37,194 --> 00:04:38,220
The police?

68
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:40,500
They want to talk about
that patient.

69
00:04:40,898 --> 00:04:42,098
Yes.

70
00:05:01,386 --> 00:05:02,589
Understood.

71
00:05:12,656 --> 00:05:14,222
Is something wrong?

72
00:05:15,470 --> 00:05:17,162
They identified the patient.

73
00:05:18,657 --> 00:05:19,999
Who was it?

74
00:05:22,836 --> 00:05:24,213
Ryuji Kanbara.

75
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:30,580
Well, at least now we know who he is.

76
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:03,450
Dr. Ashura

77
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,093
Is that true?

78
00:06:05,401 --> 00:06:06,601
Yes.

79
00:06:09,350 --> 00:06:11,450
So, how's Kanbara's condition?

80
00:06:11,710 --> 00:06:15,203
Depending on how things progress,
he may need another operation.

81
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:22,383
Bicycle-car collision.
Laceration to the left knee.

82
00:06:22,383 --> 00:06:23,656
One, two, three.

83
00:06:24,143 --> 00:06:25,776
- Unpackage.
- Starting IV.

84
00:06:25,776 --> 00:06:26,810
What's your name?

85
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:29,436
- Heavy bleeding from left leg. Suture kit.
- Okay.

86
00:06:29,436 --> 00:06:30,856
This will feel cold.

87
00:06:30,856 --> 00:06:32,069
Getting ultrasound.

88
00:06:34,491 --> 00:06:35,691
Hmm?

89
00:06:35,830 --> 00:06:39,530
Dad. Mom.

90
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,947
Dad. Mom.

91
00:06:56,046 --> 00:06:58,926
Chief. Take over the ultrasound for me.

92
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:10,096
Got it.

93
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,203
Dr. Anno.

94
00:07:23,810 --> 00:07:26,530
We can handle this patient on our own.

95
00:07:29,353 --> 00:07:30,726
Thank you.

96
00:07:40,730 --> 00:07:44,270
I've never seen Anno leave
in the middle of treatment.

97
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:47,090
Is she feeling unwell?

98
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:49,456
It didn't look like just that, though.

99
00:07:51,023 --> 00:07:52,483
Where's Dr. Anno?

100
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,716
She's doing rounds on Kanbara.

101
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:01,603
They identified the patient.

102
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:03,457
Ryuji Kanbara.

103
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:16,963
Dr. Anno.

104
00:09:23,903 --> 00:09:25,103
What do you want?

105
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:39,626
It happened 28 years ago.

106
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:42,767
The Wangan Station Stabbing Case.

107
00:09:44,546 --> 00:09:47,331
A 17-year-old boy attacked pedestrians.

108
00:09:47,596 --> 00:09:51,497
He killed three and injured over ten people.

109
00:09:53,580 --> 00:09:59,656
Under juvenile law and with extenuating
circumstances from parental abuse,

110
00:09:59,942 --> 00:10:01,856
he got life in prison.

111
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:06,177
But his parole was approved six months ago.

112
00:10:06,615 --> 00:10:08,336
He's been released.

113
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:15,293
The perpetrator's name is

114
00:10:17,613 --> 00:10:19,053
Ryuji Kanbara.

115
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,970
I was worried about you, so I looked into it.

116
00:10:27,375 --> 00:10:28,740
It was all there.

117
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:35,486
The three victims were a college student
and a young married couple.

118
00:10:36,045 --> 00:10:39,109
The couple's surname was the same as yours.

119
00:10:40,294 --> 00:10:41,502
Anno.

120
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:46,870
They were your parents, weren't they?

121
00:10:55,883 --> 00:10:57,083
Yes.

122
00:11:06,019 --> 00:11:10,280
Can you really treat someone like that?

123
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:45,050
Mom. Mom.

124
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:52,483
One child, already refused
by five hospitals.

125
00:11:52,483 --> 00:11:54,059
-
We can't.
-
Not here.

126
00:11:54,059 --> 00:11:55,212
We cannot.

127
00:11:55,212 --> 00:11:57,224
No good. We can't find a hospital.

128
00:11:57,224 --> 00:11:58,569
Taishaku General

129
00:11:59,038 --> 00:12:00,076
Yes.

130
00:12:00,076 --> 00:12:03,723
This is EMS. One child in cardiac arrest.
Requesting admission.

131
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:05,889
We can take them. Bring them now.

132
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:10,470
- Arriving in five minutes. Get ready, hurry.
- Yes, ma'am.

133
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:15,603
Emergency! A patient crashed in the ICU!

134
00:12:16,103 --> 00:12:18,490
We have a child in cardiac arrest
coming in!

135
00:12:18,490 --> 00:12:20,043
We can't go there now.

136
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:23,350
I'll go.

137
00:12:25,450 --> 00:12:27,890
Keep that patient alive until I come back.

138
00:12:28,770 --> 00:12:30,243
Chief.

139
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:33,653
- Pean clamp.
- Here.

140
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:35,640
- More pean clamps, hurry!
- Yes.

141
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,940
We're losing her.

142
00:12:36,940 --> 00:12:38,940
What about mass ligation?

143
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:41,596
No time for that.
We have to do a total resection.

144
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:43,025
Heart rate's dropping fast.

145
00:12:43,025 --> 00:12:44,560
Push more adrenaline.

146
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:46,416
Already running. No change.

147
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:47,460
Damn it!

148
00:12:47,460 --> 00:12:48,723
It's no use.

149
00:12:49,322 --> 00:12:51,075
Too much bleeding.

150
00:12:51,968 --> 00:12:54,910
We may have lost her.

151
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:57,203
There's nothing we can do.

152
00:13:02,830 --> 00:13:04,876
The patient is crying for help,

153
00:13:04,876 --> 00:13:06,710
and the doctors just give up?

154
00:13:06,845 --> 00:13:08,852
- Chief.
- Get another line in.

155
00:13:08,852 --> 00:13:11,612
Ten units whole blood.
Prep for gauze packing.

156
00:13:11,623 --> 00:13:12,838
Yes, Doctor.

157
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:18,230
You did well.

158
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:20,763
You'll be fine now.

159
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:25,243
I will save you. I promise.

160
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,710
Doctor, the bleeding...

161
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,556
- Suction.
- Yes.

162
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:42,576
Liver damage, kidney rupture,
and bowel perforation.

163
00:13:43,876 --> 00:13:45,500
With this much blood loss...

164
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:48,500
Minutes at best.

165
00:13:49,993 --> 00:13:51,230
No...

166
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:54,150
We can't stop all the bleeding
in just minutes!

167
00:14:05,103 --> 00:14:07,036
We'll do damage control surgery.

168
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,383
We can't!

169
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:11,353
- We've never done that here.
- We have no other choice.

170
00:14:14,710 --> 00:14:18,395
We'll clamp the renal artery, then
temporarily suture the liver and bowel.

171
00:14:18,395 --> 00:14:19,583
Suction.

172
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:20,630
Yes!

173
00:14:20,630 --> 00:14:21,810
Gauze packing, please.

174
00:14:21,810 --> 00:14:23,396
- Satinsky.
- Here.

175
00:14:43,236 --> 00:14:45,393
Doctor. Shura is awake.

176
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,780
Shura.

177
00:14:53,746 --> 00:14:55,132
How are you feeling?

178
00:14:57,632 --> 00:14:59,679
Where are Mom and Dad?

179
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:08,810
Your parents...

180
00:15:10,070 --> 00:15:12,541
They were taken to a different hospital.

181
00:15:14,943 --> 00:15:16,863
I'm sorry, but both of them...

182
00:15:17,243 --> 00:15:18,778
They passed away.

183
00:15:32,730 --> 00:15:34,070
No.

184
00:15:40,383 --> 00:15:41,583
No.

185
00:15:56,660 --> 00:15:58,824
Dad.

186
00:16:05,020 --> 00:16:06,780
Mom.

187
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:12,797
No.

188
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:17,156
Are you the one who saved me?

189
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:25,504
Why did you save me?

190
00:17:32,643 --> 00:17:35,883
I'm not a person who deserves to live.

191
00:17:42,752 --> 00:17:43,991
Regarding Kanbara,

192
00:17:43,991 --> 00:17:47,292
there's no improvement
in the duodenal repair site.

193
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:50,560
He'll need surgery for a full reconstruction.

194
00:17:50,562 --> 00:17:53,115
That'll be an extremely
difficult operation.

195
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:58,694
Let's do the surgery tomorrow morning.

196
00:17:59,253 --> 00:18:00,960
The lead surgeon will be...

197
00:18:06,696 --> 00:18:07,903
I'll do it.

198
00:18:10,315 --> 00:18:11,855
He's my patient.

199
00:18:13,182 --> 00:18:15,690
I can't hand this surgery off to anyone else.

200
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:21,619
Understood.

201
00:18:22,079 --> 00:18:23,939
I'll notify the OR.

202
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,679
All right, let's do this.

203
00:18:25,793 --> 00:18:26,832
Yes.

204
00:18:26,832 --> 00:18:28,166
Excuse me.

205
00:18:28,838 --> 00:18:30,658
I'm from the probation office.

206
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,860
The probation office?

207
00:18:33,020 --> 00:18:36,276
Yes. I'm here regarding
Ryuji Kanbara, who's out on parole.

208
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:48,954
Mr. Kanbara.
I'm Hayashi, your probation officer.

209
00:18:49,190 --> 00:18:50,714
This must have been awful.

210
00:18:51,810 --> 00:18:56,290
Anno had her parents murdered?

211
00:18:57,757 --> 00:19:02,610
The man who killed her parents
showed up as a patient.

212
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:07,230
No one could stay composed.

213
00:19:10,881 --> 00:19:15,130
I don't think she can handle this surgery.

214
00:19:22,524 --> 00:19:24,497
I almost died once.

215
00:19:48,010 --> 00:19:49,650
I told you, didn't I?

216
00:19:52,030 --> 00:19:54,538
My life has no value.

217
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:07,353
You heard, right?

218
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:11,400
What I did in the past.

219
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:39,103
Anno.

220
00:20:41,563 --> 00:20:45,503
I'm pulling you off of Kanbara's surgery.

221
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:49,456
Why?

222
00:20:49,810 --> 00:20:54,363
If the surgery fails
and the public finds out,

223
00:20:55,635 --> 00:20:59,498
they could accuse you of deliberately
committing malpractice for revenge.

224
00:21:01,365 --> 00:21:04,498
I can't let you take that risk.

225
00:21:24,903 --> 00:21:27,125
Shura Anno

226
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:41,129
Kanbara's surgery will proceed
as scheduled at 11:00 a.m.

227
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:49,480
I will be the lead surgeon.

228
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:53,869
Yakushiji, please assist.

229
00:21:55,929 --> 00:21:57,135
Yes, sir.

230
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:03,321
That's all. Let's do this.

231
00:22:03,603 --> 00:22:05,329
Yes, Doctor.

232
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,542
Then, the patient's condition deteriorated.

233
00:22:18,542 --> 00:22:23,070
The doctors panicked, and just when
everyone was about to give up,

234
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:25,764
yours truly, Matayoshi Kongo,
swept onto the scene,

235
00:22:25,764 --> 00:22:30,648
pulled off the surgery with superhuman skill,
and turned it all around.

236
00:22:30,648 --> 00:22:33,215
A truly historic achievement.

237
00:22:34,568 --> 00:22:36,569
They call it
"The Miracle of Taishaku."

238
00:22:36,569 --> 00:22:39,736
That's amazing, Chief Kongo!

239
00:22:43,140 --> 00:22:44,530
Excuse me, sir.

240
00:22:45,885 --> 00:22:48,451
This area is restricted to
authorized personnel.

241
00:22:48,451 --> 00:22:52,952
Oh, I'm sorry.
I got a bit turned around.

242
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:59,341
I see. If you're here to visit
a patient, the ward is that way.

243
00:23:00,026 --> 00:23:03,273
Oh, that helps. Thank you.

244
00:23:03,273 --> 00:23:04,486
You're welcome.

245
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:10,480
I, Kongo Matayoshi, have experienced
what they call miracles four times.

246
00:23:10,540 --> 00:23:11,565
Four times?

247
00:23:11,565 --> 00:23:14,773
The Spring Miracle, the Summer Miracle,
the Autumn Miracle...

248
00:23:32,219 --> 00:23:33,511
What do you want?

249
00:23:36,760 --> 00:23:43,316
I saw your medical records from 28 years ago.

250
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:47,119
Okay.

251
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:50,705
During my two months
of training in emergency medicine,

252
00:23:53,650 --> 00:23:59,324
I learned so much from you, Dr. Anno.

253
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:10,210
No matter who the patient is, you give
everything to save the life before you.

254
00:24:12,850 --> 00:24:18,243
You taught me that that's what it means
to be an emergency physician.

255
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:29,056
I'm just a resident.

256
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:37,720
But I'm prepared for this.

257
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:48,520
We will complete Mr. Kanbara's surgery.
I promise.

258
00:25:28,488 --> 00:25:30,315
Resident

259
00:25:40,676 --> 00:25:45,180
I never imagined the child from back then
would come back as a resident.

260
00:25:47,753 --> 00:25:50,550
I'd already decided
I will work at this hospital.

261
00:25:53,529 --> 00:25:55,836
I will become an ER doctor.

262
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,300
When that incident happened,

263
00:26:02,710 --> 00:26:05,496
I was turned away by hospital after hospital.

264
00:26:06,855 --> 00:26:08,776
I'd almost given up.

265
00:26:12,410 --> 00:26:14,269
The reason I survived was because

266
00:26:15,749 --> 00:26:18,003
I had the luck to be brought here

267
00:26:19,989 --> 00:26:21,943
and you happened to be here.

268
00:26:26,323 --> 00:26:31,543
I will become an emergency physician
just like you.

269
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:40,366
Whether someone like you
or your parents lives or dies

270
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:47,930
should never be left to luck or chance.

271
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:57,150
No matter where patients are taken,
no matter which doctor sees them, they live.

272
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:02,380
We need to build that kind of
emergency care system.

273
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:13,000
There's a doctor in our ER
who's working hard to do just that.

274
00:27:14,520 --> 00:27:15,906
Chief Tamon.

275
00:27:17,043 --> 00:27:21,556
Study well under him.

276
00:27:27,790 --> 00:27:28,990
Yes, ma'am.

277
00:27:35,150 --> 00:27:37,072
- Too slow.
- Yes, sir.

278
00:27:38,303 --> 00:27:40,563
- Raise the blade angle a bit more.
- Yes.

279
00:27:41,050 --> 00:27:42,256
Anno.

280
00:27:43,570 --> 00:27:45,563
- Right there.
- Okay.

281
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:50,880
Right acute subdural hematoma?

282
00:27:50,986 --> 00:27:52,713
Intracranial pressure is rising.

283
00:27:52,713 --> 00:27:54,983
Brain herniation will stop his breathing.

284
00:27:54,983 --> 00:27:57,150
Craniotomy now
to evacuate the hematoma.

285
00:28:11,620 --> 00:28:12,820
Still at it?

286
00:28:13,019 --> 00:28:14,252
Yes.

287
00:28:15,660 --> 00:28:17,145
Too tense.

288
00:28:17,744 --> 00:28:19,766
Relax your fingers and try again.

289
00:28:19,766 --> 00:28:20,970
Yes.

290
00:28:23,130 --> 00:28:24,902
Yes, that's right. Yes.

291
00:28:25,770 --> 00:28:27,822
Understood. I'm on my way.

292
00:28:28,098 --> 00:28:30,904
Emergency call from Surgery.

293
00:28:31,202 --> 00:28:34,030
Aortic dissection.
They're short-handed so I'll help out.

294
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:35,276
Understood.

295
00:28:35,595 --> 00:28:38,570
I won't be back till morning.
I'll leave things here to you.

296
00:28:38,570 --> 00:28:39,780
Yes, sir.

297
00:28:50,136 --> 00:28:52,446
- Yes.
-
Two trauma patients incoming.

298
00:28:52,532 --> 00:28:55,941
One high school girl with
a penetrating wound from back to abdomen.

299
00:28:55,941 --> 00:28:59,127
The other is male.
Self-inflicted stab wound to the chest.

300
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:01,291
Self-inflicted? What do you mean?

301
00:29:01,294 --> 00:29:02,810
A random stabbing attack.

302
00:29:03,623 --> 00:29:08,257
After stabbing the girl,
the attacker stabbed himself in the chest.

303
00:29:08,483 --> 00:29:12,259
Multiple hospitals have already refused.
We can't find anyone to take them.

304
00:29:12,259 --> 00:29:15,179
Both are in shock.
Please accept them.

305
00:29:18,430 --> 00:29:19,823
Bring them both in.

306
00:29:46,416 --> 00:29:48,163
Doctor, will you be all right?

307
00:29:48,569 --> 00:29:51,528
The liver damage is too deep.
I can't stop the bleeding.

308
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,607
Administer adrenaline.

309
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:05,856
No good. No response to adrenaline.

310
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:07,800
How is he?

311
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:11,340
No heartbeat.

312
00:30:11,553 --> 00:30:13,513
Ten minutes since cardiac arrest.

313
00:30:56,030 --> 00:30:57,703
Get the thoracotomy set.

314
00:30:58,450 --> 00:30:59,916
This one still has a chance.

315
00:30:59,916 --> 00:31:02,023
Doctor, what about the girl?

316
00:31:02,023 --> 00:31:03,430
She's bleeding too much.

317
00:31:03,470 --> 00:31:05,908
But she's the victim!

318
00:31:05,908 --> 00:31:09,716
If we prioritize her now,
we'll lose them both!

319
00:31:11,974 --> 00:31:13,327
Thoracotomy set. Hurry.

320
00:31:13,421 --> 00:31:14,621
Okay.

321
00:31:16,490 --> 00:31:18,032
More blood and adrenaline too.

322
00:31:18,032 --> 00:31:19,232
Got it.

323
00:31:22,551 --> 00:31:23,784
I'll take over.

324
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:27,190
Cutting the clothes.

325
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:35,623
Why didn't you save my daughter?!

326
00:31:37,240 --> 00:31:42,220
The stab wound damaged her liver
and inferior vena cava.

327
00:31:44,590 --> 00:31:46,526
We couldn't restore her heartbeat.

328
00:31:55,600 --> 00:31:56,919
Why?

329
00:31:58,300 --> 00:32:01,190
Why did our daughter die?

330
00:32:01,810 --> 00:32:03,903
Why's that man alive?

331
00:32:08,203 --> 00:32:10,656
Give her back to me!

332
00:32:13,310 --> 00:32:15,096
Bring her back!

333
00:32:39,030 --> 00:32:40,963
No matter who the patient is,

334
00:32:42,176 --> 00:32:44,996
we do everything we can
to save the life before us.

335
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,443
That's our duty as emergency physicians.

336
00:32:53,597 --> 00:32:55,184
Your call was right.

337
00:32:57,770 --> 00:32:59,176
Well done.

338
00:34:23,312 --> 00:34:25,464
Director

339
00:34:28,446 --> 00:34:29,704
What is it?

340
00:34:44,223 --> 00:34:45,917
Duodenal reconstruction complete.

341
00:34:45,917 --> 00:34:48,592
- Moving to irrigation and closure.
- Yes, Doctor.

342
00:34:52,510 --> 00:34:55,770
Dr. Daikoku.
BP is spiking and heart rate is dropping.

343
00:34:55,770 --> 00:34:58,190
How? He was stable just a moment ago.

344
00:34:59,276 --> 00:35:02,103
No bleeding anywhere.
What's going on?

345
00:35:26,090 --> 00:35:27,390
Dr. Anno.

346
00:35:36,296 --> 00:35:39,056
Right pupil is fixed.
No light reflex.

347
00:35:41,230 --> 00:35:44,303
Suspected rupture and occlusion
of right internal carotid.

348
00:35:46,755 --> 00:35:48,262
Dissection-related stroke.

349
00:35:49,570 --> 00:35:52,209
The impact damaged the carotid artery,

350
00:35:52,209 --> 00:35:55,363
and the aneurysm ruptured
while occluding, causing a stroke.

351
00:35:55,410 --> 00:35:58,190
We need endovascular treatment now
or he won't make it.

352
00:35:58,190 --> 00:35:59,829
The cath lab is occupied.

353
00:35:59,829 --> 00:36:02,123
I'll repair the carotid now.

354
00:36:02,636 --> 00:36:04,283
- Prep for surgery.
- Yes.

355
00:36:05,334 --> 00:36:06,601
Let's close the abdomen.

356
00:36:06,601 --> 00:36:07,801
Yes, sir.

357
00:36:20,363 --> 00:36:22,523
Why did you save me again?

358
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:27,690
I should have just died.

359
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:40,736
I've witnessed countless deaths here.

360
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:47,390
People who never got to see tomorrow.

361
00:36:58,493 --> 00:37:00,793
People have value simply by being alive.

362
00:37:08,782 --> 00:37:10,130
Even you.

363
00:37:16,453 --> 00:37:18,166
That's what I want to believe.

364
00:38:21,563 --> 00:38:23,596
Please take care.

365
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:26,071
Please be careful.

366
00:38:29,385 --> 00:38:30,586
I will.

367
00:38:34,610 --> 00:38:36,269
Where is the female doctor?

368
00:38:39,348 --> 00:38:42,309
Dr. Anno is currently in surgery.

369
00:38:45,686 --> 00:38:46,912
Well then...

370
00:38:48,100 --> 00:38:49,829
I have a request.

371
00:38:51,053 --> 00:38:52,259
Yes?

372
00:39:31,657 --> 00:39:33,303
Someone from the TV station

373
00:39:33,303 --> 00:39:35,043
28 years: Victim Families

374
00:39:35,043 --> 00:39:37,724
told me you were at Taishaku.

375
00:39:41,820 --> 00:39:44,083
This is for my daughter!

376
00:40:02,739 --> 00:40:04,459
You have

377
00:40:05,659 --> 00:40:08,818
no right to be alive.

378
00:40:30,497 --> 00:40:31,856
Operation in Progress

379
00:41:02,050 --> 00:41:04,976
He was already in cardiac arrest
at the scene.

380
00:41:06,595 --> 00:41:11,535
He showed no response to resuscitation
and was pronounced dead.

381
00:41:38,296 --> 00:41:41,555
Human life is so fleeting.

382
00:41:46,196 --> 00:41:47,522
Mr. Kanbara.

383
00:41:48,842 --> 00:41:52,370
He left a message for you
before he was discharged.

384
00:41:54,711 --> 00:41:58,098
He said you were the first person
to treat him as a human being.

385
00:41:59,906 --> 00:42:02,050
The very first.

386
00:42:04,852 --> 00:42:06,069
Oh.

387
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:10,706
And also...

388
00:42:12,816 --> 00:42:15,369
He wanted to apologize for what he did.

389
00:42:16,943 --> 00:42:18,143
What?

390
00:42:18,513 --> 00:42:22,520
He knew you were that girl from back then.

391
00:42:23,663 --> 00:42:25,343
Apparently he realized it.

392
00:42:36,457 --> 00:42:38,823
Shura Anno

393
00:42:46,650 --> 00:42:48,900
It was because you saved his life.

394
00:42:50,867 --> 00:42:54,510
I believe that's what allowed him
to face his sins.

395
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:57,590
But

396
00:42:58,750 --> 00:43:03,950
if I hadn't saved him,
none of this would have happened.

397
00:43:09,539 --> 00:43:10,759
You're right.

398
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:16,000
Even so...

399
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:21,040
If there's a life fighting
to survive right before you,

400
00:43:22,496 --> 00:43:24,396
you save it without hesitation.

401
00:43:27,302 --> 00:43:29,502
And you'll keep doing that, won't you?

402
00:43:34,770 --> 00:43:36,630
It's all I know how to do.

403
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:11,371
- I'm his wife.
- Misuzu?

404
00:44:11,371 --> 00:44:12,475
What?!

405
00:44:12,475 --> 00:44:13,531
Don't say that!

406
00:44:13,531 --> 00:44:15,100
Bring them here now!
